                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12659611" author="stack" created="Mon, 29 Dec 2008 19:22:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I thought this was supposed to have been fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-927&quot; title=&quot;We don&amp;#39;t recover if HRS hosting -ROOT-/.META. goes down&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-927&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-927&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12659626" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 29 Dec 2008 19:56:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All my mapreduce tasks were stalled in TIF getting split assignments. On the browser, master UI was stuck in refresh. Had several HRS go down in succession with OOME. A good test would be to take down the HRS hosting ROOT and META, then take down another, and another, before and after recovery. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12660004" author="jimk" created="Wed, 31 Dec 2008 02:02:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The master stays up through all this and does not crash?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12660007" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 31 Dec 2008 02:25:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It stays up but is stalled. I think the master UI main page stuck in refresh is telling. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12660025" author="stack" created="Wed, 31 Dec 2008 06:07:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is message from up on list:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Date: Mon, 29 Dec 2008 13:27:48 -0500
From: g00dn3ss &amp;lt;g00dn3ss@gmail.com&amp;gt;
To: hbase-user@hadoop.apache.org
Subject: Re: Recovering HBase after HDFS Corruption


...Then I restart the
system.  Some of the regionservers get &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;FileNotFound&quot;&lt;/span&gt; exceptions when
looking &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; some of the corrupted files.  Then the affected regionservers
shut down.   So I don&apos;t understand how the problem I&apos;m seeing could be
caused by having something in memory that doesn&apos;t match what&apos;s on disk &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; I
am starting the entire system from scratch.

The other issue that causes further problems in &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; is when one of
these problematic regions is on the same regionserver as the -ROOT- region.
When the regionserver holding the -ROOT- region crashes, the entire system
seems to go down.  Is &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; what
http:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1080 is about?
&lt;/span&gt;...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12661308" author="stack" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2009 20:50:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is pretty easy to reproduce.  I just tried it.  In my cluster, &lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt; and .META. were on different servers.  I just kill &lt;del&gt;9d the regionserver hosting -ROOT&lt;/del&gt;.  Master seems to hang splitting log.  Upload sort of goes on because lots of places have .META. cached but other places are hung up waiting on a &lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12661311" author="stack" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2009 20:54:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm... &lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt; sort of got deployed but only after another regionserver went into the hell cycle of FileNotFoundException: File does not exist: hdfs://XX.XX.powerset.com:9000/hbasetrunk2/TestTable/1310771879/info/mapfiles/1091203795887123280/index which I&apos;m pretty sure is result of double-assignment of regions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12661318" author="stack" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2009 21:00:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cluster is pretty much hosed.  Got some illegal state transitions too in master log.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12662218" author="jimk" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2009 01:49:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed with changes for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1104&quot; title=&quot;Doubly-assigned regions redux&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1104&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1104&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
